      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues - Must fix before merge] Line 640: The simulator returns success for dropped RTP packets without updating normal send-path state such as sequence/byte accounting that may happen inside `writeData()`. This makes the sender believe packets were transmitted while bypassing any side effects in the real path, which can skew RTCP/QoS measurements and make tests validate behavior that production would not exercise. Prefer placing the simulator at the lowest send point inside/around `writeData()` after normal RTP bookkeeping, or explicitly preserve the same side effects before dropping.",
